  "title": "Accounts Executive (Ship Owner)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Handle full set of accounts including AR, AP, and GL</p></li><li><p>Prepare journal entries, process invoices and payments, and track receipts</p></li><li><p>Perform month-, quarter-, and year-end closing and bank reconciliations</p></li><li><p>Follow up on outstanding balances with customers and internal teams</p></li><li><p>Maintain fixed assets and asset registers</p></li><li><p>Assist with cash flow monitoring and reporting</p></li><li><p>Upload payment files via the bank’s e-banking system</p></li><li><p>Prepare audit schedules and liaise with external auditors</p></li><li><p>Compile MPA Local Business Spending reports</p></li><li><p>Maintain proper accounting documentation and records</p></li><li><p>Work closely with other departments to ensure accurate accounting</p></li><li><p>Provide backup support and handle ad-hoc administrative / IT duties when required</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Diploma or higher qualification in Accounting or equivalent</p></li><li><p>Minimum 5 years of accounting experience</p></li><li><p>At least 3 years of relevant experience in the maritime industry (Ship Owner / Operator preferred)</p></li><li><p>Proficient in MS Office, especially Excel, and familiar with accounting systems</p></li><li><p>Good communication skills and a detail-oriented, independent team player</p></li></ul>",
